document.title: 2020 New Jersey Student Learning Standards – Visual and Performing Arts

9AABD285AFE649B5A814B6ECBCCFB0EB.description:
Demonstrate understanding of relationships between music and the other arts,
other disciplines, varied contexts, and daily life.

EB20DFB8726C4F7BB36F1CB3DF06733F.description:
Demonstrate understanding of relationships between music and the other arts,
other disciplines, varied contexts, and daily life.

A67AD131076A41A1B3914AC16A71336A.description:
Demonstrate understanding of relationships between music and the other arts,
other disciplines, varied contexts and daily life.

532EA4A354EF42E0B3F243092B97893F.description:
Relating artistic ideas and works within societal, cultural and
historical contexts to deepen understanding.

956B466A8E6D4D33AF8B7B951FAB7698.description:
Demonstrate how interests, knowledge and skills related to personal choices and
intent when creating, performing and responding to music.

45A552FEB18C4FB99630E57C892566DF.description:
Demonstrate how interests, knowledge and skills relate to personal choices and
intent when creating, performing and responding to music.

6691E16DDDAB4FE79EC3890483855B82.description:
Demonstrate how interests, knowledge, and skills relate to personal choices and
intent when creating, performing, and responding to music.

2BB1CC90EE364EEAAE650C502A1D4263.description:
Synthesizing and relating knowledge and personal experiences to
create products.

D664CE40EC2F42A59E03B13B56F5A43E.description:
Develop and justify the evaluation of a variety of music based on established and
personally developed criteria, digital, electronic and analog features, and understanding of purpose
and context.

C0928419E74D422D9381F549D8F6FFAB.description:
Apply criteria to evaluate music based on analysis, interpretation, artistic intent,
digital, electronic, and analog features, and musical qualities.

BDB82ABF0415431BA2297A130FBD3660.description:
Evaluate music using criteria based on analysis, interpretation, digital and
electronic features, and personal interests.

BD062A0B25FC49FABEF8421F3BCEAB67.description:
Examine and cite research from multiple sources to connect the influence of the
elements of music, digital and electronic features, context, purpose, and other art forms to the
expressive intent of musical works.

450999A683F240B8896C2EFC3E86786D.description:
Connect the influence of the elements of music, digital and electronic features,
context, purpose, and other art forms to the expressive intent of musical works.

812AC73015294368B2B75E58CC9115C4.description:
Explain and support an interpretation of the expressive intent of musical selections
based on treatment of the elements of music, digital and electronic features, and purpose.

E00AAFAFC1944E56939FD2E7E5F96973.description:
Justify (by using examples) how an analysis of the structural characteristics,
context, and technological and creative decisions, informs interest in and response to the music.

4FDFBFB484A941CA86B90F651823C581.description:
Select, describe and compare a variety of musical selections based on
characteristics and knowledge of the music, understanding of digital and electronic aspects, and the
purpose and context of the works.

916349E5841F41EE88737133AB1961C4.description:
Explain how an analysis of the structure, context and technological aspects of the
music informs the response.

79E8ED40E7084E0EBDFCEB446D2C0E04.description:
Select and critique contrasting musical works, defending opinions based on
manipulations of the elements of music, digital and electronic aspects, and the purpose and context of
the works.

9EB0EB9005C54016975BB394BDA1C4CE.description:
Explain how knowledge of the structure (e.g., repetition, similarities, contrasts),
technological aspects, and purpose of the music informs the response.

67C3E1BFA16A4F158DEBBA054F02476D.description:
Cite reasons for choosing music based on the use of the elements of music, digital
and electronic aspects, and connections to interest or purpose.

AB908DDCF8AD44B4B5E52C4B929A22B8.description:
Demonstrate an ability to connect with audience members before and engaging with
and responding to them during prepared and improvised performances.

F5E2FF7AE27A407EABDA98ADC1F30EF9.description:
Integrating digital and analog tools and resources, demonstrate an understanding
and attention to technical accuracy and expressive qualities of the music in prepared and improvised
performances of a varied repertoire of music representing diverse cultures, styles, genres, and
historical periods.

786C8E31DCA340E0B6EB20D8C946275B.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of the expressive intent when connecting with an
audience through prepared and improvised performances.

0957D542028644C0A1AAF623DFFB9BE4.description:
Using digital tools and resources, demonstrate technical accuracy and expressive
qualities in prepared and improvised performances of a varied repertoire of music representing
diverse cultures, styles, and genres.

B8EA4542152940BE969FF4337E81B921.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of the context of music through prepared and
improvised performances.

81D9BDA32A7E485FB875727A83ABD06E.description:
Using digital tools, demonstrate attention to technical accuracy and expressive
qualities in prepared and improvised performances of a varied repertoire of music.

6271CF39A70041ACB0CEAA982817F153.description:
Apply appropriate criteria as well as feedback from multiple sources and develop
and implement varied strategies to improve and refine the technical and expressive aspects of
prepared and improvised performances in varied programs of music.

4060244AC7CF49C8BBC793F855CC4917.description:
Develop and implement rehearsal strategies to improve and refine the technical and
expressive aspects of prepared and improvised performances in a varied repertoire of music.

B9F2C8BCF9874722BB2A1487EF395857.description:
Identify and implement rehearsal strategies to improve the technical and expressive
aspects of prepared and improvised performances in a varied repertoire of music.

5F9EA4E5386D4C4EB602BFEAAF08697C.description:
Developing and refining techniques and models or steps needed to
create products.

ADC34926FA7C477AB4FB5B692F959AFC.description:
Demonstrate how understanding the style, genre, context, and integration of digital
technologies in a varied repertoire of music informs and influences prepared and improvised
performances and their ability to connect with audiences.

5DCBD39D7AB548CC819FC525527482C3.description:
Examine, evaluate and critique how context, musical aspects of the composition
and digital media/tools inform prepared and improvised performances.

0543C7E09D6E41BB8C22983CFA7CB258.description:
Develop and apply criteria to select varied programs to study and perform based on
interest, an understanding of the musical characteristics, expressive challenges in the music, and the
performer’s musical skill using digital tools and resources.

F1CAE6DAD06540AEAFD6EFB562007836.description:
Demonstrate how understanding the style, genre, context, and use of digital tools
and resources in a varied repertoire of music influences prepared or improvised performances and
performers’ ability to connect with audiences.

B1605BB6A89148068E0C8D331EA741AA.description:
Describe and provide examples of how context, musical aspects of the composition,
and digital media/tools inform prepared and improvised performances.

78BC1A9EEF60462688E7062DEA878B8F.description:
Develop and apply criteria to select sound resources to study and perform based on
interest, an understanding of musical characteristics of the music, and the performer’s musical skill
using digital tools and resources.

8D766421AF2E45A0B741A9EDCD03FF58.description:
Identify the context, expressive challenges, and use of digital tools in a varied
repertoire of music influence prepared or improvised performances.

C7E8DB9C102B451A9C95546D7924574D.description:
Describe how context, structural aspects of the music, and digital media/tools
inform prepared and improvised performances.

3BCE1E8DA9E740278600A8FE5FCCB1F9.description:
Develop and explain the criteria used for selecting varied sound resources based on
interest, music reading skills, and an understanding of the performer’s musical and technological
skill.

4079468FE41447B4B7F2189B4371A8BD.description:
Share a portfolio of musical creations representing varied styles and genres that
demonstrates musical and technological craftsmanship as well as the use of digital and/or analog tools
and resources in developing and organizing musical ideas.

0D1CD022BB4B42C196F7A07ADBEE08BE.description:
Develop and implement varied strategies and apply appropriate criteria to improve
and refine the technical and expressive aspects of draft compositions and improvisations.

55F82A02C02F462DAC52CF77AE16C9E4.description:
Share compositions and improvisations that demonstrate musical and technological
craftsmanship as well as the use of digital and/or analog tools and resources in developing and
organizing musical ideas.

23D359F6CFCD41E2A737FEE7462A2F4E.description:
Develop and implement varied strategies to improve and refine the technical and
expressive aspects of draft compositions and improvisations.

E46C1DCA690B4225A2B9D11A0DBFAFE7.description:
Share compositions or improvisations that demonstrate musical and technological
craftsmanship as well as the use of digital tools and resources in developing and organizing musical
ideas.

B295F1798EBD4FBD9B2537F93B0007C2.description:
Drawing on feedback from teachers and peers, develop and implement strategies to
improve and refine the technical and expressive aspects of draft compositions and improvisations.

759A217D7AD3412D9E030DF8BED2C753.description:
Select, develop and organize multiple melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas to
develop into a larger work that exhibits unity, variety, complexity, and coherence using digital and/or
analog tools and resources.

72CA108DD1204AE8A15FE8778C699F9F.description:
Select melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas to develop into a larger work that
exhibits unity and variety using digital and/or analog tools.

1F40F2FE23804CF6AF35C22D77F38824.description:
Select melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas to develop into a larger work using
digital tools and resources.

0E296C457DD643CFA0AC889AE9E13330.description:
Generate melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas for compositions and
improvisations that incorporate digital tools and resources.

8D6CFEE5265B4473962C6461C8CD6204.description: Generate melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas for compositions or improvisations using digital tools and resources.

BA1E57130EC646E89F891C47F4625AF1.description: Generate melodic, rhythmic and harmonic ideas for compositions or improvisations using digital tools.
